          "E-Learning",
          "End of Course Performance",
          "At-risk (0) & Marginal (1) vs Not at-risk (3)",
          "32593 students",
          "7 Course in OULAD",
          "Module presentation, LMS logs, Student Demograohics",
          "Unclear",
          "End of Course",
          "Authors develop a SVM model that takes a OULAD dataset. \n\nThe important thing to understand about RTV-SVM is that it aims to reduce the number of observations to consider for SVM:\n\nIt starts with identifying the multivariate normal distribution of the data for each class and selecting the N obervations with the lowest probability of belonging to the distribution (because they would be near the margin). Then, it calculates a ratio to decide how many central points would can be removed safely - The Tier-1 elimination of training stage.\n\nThen, it draws an imaginary line between the center of class 1 and of class 0 and projects each point according to this line. Points away from the boundary are eliminated. \n\nIt then Runs a standard SVM on the remaining observations.",
          "RTV-SVM-no elimination\n\nRTV-SVM-T1 elimination\n\nRTV-SVM-T2 elimination\n\nRTV-SVM-t1+T2 elimination\n\n",
