    {
      "id": "dab3e24d-ed29-4b63-ade0-b994c9781a34",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "In their empyrical experiment, the authors resort to 33 thousand students in 7 courses. The proposed model managed to a 60% reduction of vector size without compromising predictive performance. Moreover, the proposed model also achieved 90%+ accuracies for the identification of at-risk or maginal students. Also, the authors seem to use OULAD.",
